  {
    "Id": "129756",
    "ThreadId": "39115",
    "Html": "<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\">I did not see this feature in Combo Box column in DataGrid v1, but maybe I’m wrong; in regular Combo Box it handles by combination of properties IsReadOnly and IsEditable, see</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.windows.controls.combobox.iseditable.aspx\"><span style=\"color:#800080\">http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.windows.controls.combobox.iseditable.aspx</span></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\">What you can do, replace <span style=\"color:#993300\">DataGridComboBoxColumn</span> with <span style=\"font-size:10pt;color:#a31515;font-family:'courier new'\">DataGridTemplateColumn </span><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'courier new'\">and for <span style=\"color:#a31515\">DataGridTemplateColumn.CellTemplate in DataTemplate </span>have regular ComboBox with those properties set as you neded, and set Auto Complete feature as you want to. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'courier new'\">                                   Thanks. Lena</span></p>\r\n",
    "PostedDate": "2008-11-03T12:42:07.597-08:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
